  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose-wrap prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Work</p>
      <h1>Where I've worked</h1>
      <p>
        The short version: audit-grade rigor from EY, strategy consulting
        delivered to household-name clients, and hands-on analytics inside a
        Fortune 500 utility. The full detail is in my
        <a href="/Andreas_Jackson_Resume.pdf">resume</a>. These are the three
        stories I'd tell first.
      </p>

      <h2>Ernst &amp; Young</h2>
      <p class="role-line">
        FSO Assurance Associate, Banking &amp; Capital Markets · San Francisco
        · 2026 to present
      </p>
      <p>
        I work in EY's financial services assurance practice, analyzing
        financial statements, reconciliations, and internal controls across 3
        to 4 concurrent banking engagements. The job is finding the variances
        and material findings that matter and writing them up in risk
        summaries that client CFOs and leadership act on. It's where I learned
        that a number isn't done until you can defend how it was built, a
        standard I apply to everything on this site.
      </p>

      <h2>Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation</h2>
      <p class="role-line">
        Strategy Project Manager (contract, via ABA Consulting) · 2024
      </p>
      <p>
        The Foundation needed to decide which partner organizations could
        actually carry a major initiative. I built a quantitative
        partner-scoring framework from scratch, grounded in 30+ peer-reviewed
        sources and 10+ expert interviews, then led a cross-functional team of
        8 analysts across 5 simultaneous workstreams to assess 6 prospective
        partners. Six months of research came down to one deliverable: a
        ranked shortlist and an actionable investment thesis, presented
        directly to the Foundation's Manager of Strategy.
      </p>

      <h2>Southern California Edison</h2>
      <p class="role-line">Asset Data &amp; Strategy Implementation Intern · 2023</p>
      <p>
        Inside Edison International's asset strategy group, I designed an
        Excel operations database that automated the team's efficiency and
        headcount modeling, improving team productivity by 75%, and built
        Power BI dashboards that gave leadership a live view of asset KPIs.
        Small team, big company, and a lesson in how much leverage one good
        internal tool creates.
      </p>

